==English==

===Noun===
'''blues''', plural '''blues'''

# (''colloquial'') A feeling of sadness or depression.  Generally used with ''the''.
#: ''My trainwreck of a love-life gives me the blues.''
# (''colloquial'') One's particular life experience, particularly including the hardships one has faced.
#: ''Your blues is just like mine.''
#: ''Your blues are just like mine.''
# A musical form, African-American in origin, generally featuring an eight-bar or twelve-bar structure and using the [[blues scale]].  Often used with ''the''.
#: ''Many great blues musicians come from the Mississippi Delta region.''
#: ''A large portion of modern popular music is influenced by the blues.''
# (''music, always singular'') A musical composition following blues forms.
#: ''My next number is a blues in G.''

===Usage Note===
Despite its plural form, ''blues'' may be gramatically singular or plural, except where noted.

